Where a circuit breaker is used as a load break disconnection device, it shallâ€”
(a) meet the requirements of Clause 4.3.6.2;
(b) be rated according to Clause 4.3.4.2.5; and
(c) meet the requirements for isolation, including marking requirements for an isolation device, in accordance with AS/NZS 60898.2 or AS/NZS IEC 60947.2.
(d) interrupt all live conductors simultaneously (i.e. have at least one pole per polarity);
Enclosures for circuit breakers shall be IP rated according to Clause 4.4.6.
